{
  "text": "Similarly, underplated structure has been observed at other volcanic rifted margins, e.g. in the Central Atlantic [CITATION_1] , South Atlantic [CITATION_2] , parts of the South China Sea where the Vp/Vs ratio is also very high [CITATION_3] , and the polar Alpha Ridge [CITATION_4] . However, the coverage by seismic profiles at other margins is sparser than in the North Atlantic Ocean. Seismic data indicate that some volcanic margins may not have been subject to underplating of the stretched continental crust, e.g. at the Labrador Sea [CITATION_5] and the northern South China Sea [CITATION_6] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
